      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 118,
      "message": "The \"version\" here comes from the \"dcae_cli data_format\ngenerate name:version...\" command entered by the user on the\ncommand line.  If the user does not enter a version, then the\noutput is generated as follows:\n    self\": {\n        \"description\": \"\", \n        \"name\": \"tom-test\", \n        \"version\": \"\"\n    }.....\nI assume if it is omitted, then the null, in the string\nconcatenation that follows in the code, will nullify the\nstring.\n\nNote: I just removed the trailing blank space in this line,\nsince it was showing as a red block, which you had previously\nnoted. ;",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4355,
        "name": "Tom Bednarski",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "tb2541@att.com",
        "username": "tb2541onap"
      },
      "updated": "2018-10-04 17:46:35.000000000",
